<br>
For anybody of you who ever played EQ, you might remember &quot;Double Attack&quot;. That was the skill to swing your weapon twice while attacking with your weapon.<br>
<br>
That would be exactly how I see a Blademaster! A double wielding, maybe double swinging whirlwind of steel.<br>
<br>
With the Double Attack skill, you &quot;could&quot; do up to 4 attacks when swingin both weapons.<br>
<br>
Give double attack only to BM's (at least in Hib, maybe this might be a good idea for Mercs as well). This way you could increase BM's without buffing Shades/Rangers too much.<br>
<br>
Style damage would still only count for the main hand's first attack (no change there).<br>
<br>
Percentage of the chance to land a double attack could be based on either weapon skill or cd. Or both.<br>
<br>
Interested to hear what you think.<br>
<br>
